# Language Conventions

## Code (ALWAYS English)

- Variable names, function names, class names: English
- TypeScript interfaces, enums, DTOs: English
- API endpoints and route paths: English
- Database table and column names: English
- Git commit messages: English (conventional commits)
- Code comments: English

## UI/UX (ALWAYS Catalan)

- All user-facing text: Catalan (títols, botons, missatges, labels, placeholders)
- Error messages shown to users: Catalan
- Email/notification content: Catalan
- Documentation for end-users: Catalan

## Developer Documentation

- Technical docs (specs, architecture): English preferred, Catalan acceptable
- README and contributing guides: Catalan (target audience is the colla)

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — English code, Catalan UI
interface AttendanceStatus {
  CONFIRMED = 'CONFIRMED',
  DECLINED = 'DECLINED',
  PENDING = 'PENDING',
}

const labels: Record<AttendanceStatus, string> = {
  [AttendanceStatus.CONFIRMED]: 'Vinc',
  [AttendanceStatus.DECLINED]: 'No vinc',
  [AttendanceStatus.PENDING]: 'Pendent',
};

// ❌ BAD — Catalan in code
interface EstatAssistencia {
  PUC_ANAR = 'PUC_ANAR',
}
```
